weekly_note.summary: Week 11 featured several narrow outcomes and a handful of matchup-swinging performances from unexpected sources. Multiple teams benefited from high D/ST or kicker outputs (Steelers D/ST 22.0, Jaguars D/ST 12.0, Jason Myers 14.0) and bench players who outscored typical starters (Travis Kelce 19.6 on bench, Christian Watson 18.6 on bench, Jameson Williams 17.7 on bench). Conversely, several projected high scorers failed to deliver (Lamar Jackson, Josh Jacobs, Ja'Marr Chase, Sam Darnold), skewing results. There were multiple close finishes (Gronk for my johnson by ~1.5, Baker's Brownie Stand by ~1.8), demonstrating how single player decisions (benching a hot player or starting a defense) materially affected outcomes.
notable_trends: Bench management mattered: several teams left players on the bench who significantly outscored starters (Travis Kelce, Christian Watson, Jameson Williams).
D/ST and kickers swung matchups: Steelers D/ST (22.0) and kickers like Tyler Loop and Jason Myers outperformed and were decisive.
High variance at skill positions: multiple RBs/WRs had very large positive or negative deviations from projections, producing several upsets and close games.
